&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ACP%20Training%20Series.png" alt="The 3 courses in the ACP Training Series are (1) Engaging Stakeholders (2) Contextualized Instruction and (3) Bridge Programs" width="400" height="311" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_right"&gt;Welcome to Instructional Considerations for Adult Career Pathways&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This course and the accompanying materials were developed by Heather Turngren in collaboration with the American Institutes for Research. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This course will take about 3 hours to complete.&amp;nbsp;Please note, items with solid boxes can be self-checked to indicate completion; however, the self-assessment and all learning checks are graded and required for completion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is one in a &lt;span&gt;series&lt;/span&gt; of three self-directed courses focusing on career pathways and is intended for adult basic education (ABE) and English language acquisition (ELA) &amp;nbsp;instructors and other education professionals teaching or developing
